<br>
They wouldn't hand them out like candy on Test and get the rest of the community in a tizzy, because we all know from experience there's a 99% chance that things on Test will go Live.<br>
<br>
If they find the item to be horribly unbalancing, no <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> real</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> harm done because only one wizard per server has one.  I suppose they could have simply made an item with Flowing Thought X on it but I think that would have snowballed into the wizard community ecstatic that, &quot;They're putting FT10 on items now!&quot;  It would have also been a fairly obvious test.<br>
<br>
I dunno, just a thought I wanted to throw out. <p>Lady Sinari Dax<br>
The Platinum Queen<br>
High Council of The Companions
Veeshan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urealwing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Realwing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ultradbz.net/buttons/mybutton.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 4:27:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scepter of Al'Kabor as a testing tool?</span><hr size=1> I think its more of a flowing thought 3 or 5 myself, no items have been found with a flowing thought over 2 it think. Heh never know i don't think verant is that smart enough for advanced tactics like that yet... or maybe thats what they want me to thing /raise <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umadleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 5:46:25 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.packetlost.com/ho/im/headache.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scepter of Al'Kabor as a testing tool?</span><hr size=1> It's already been ripped apart. The effect is 10 mana regen per tick which would be equivalent to a FT 10, it just has a fancy name.<br>
