Level 60 Sorceror<BR>
Terris - Thule<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvulpdiscoinferno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vulp DiscoInferno</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://freepages.ugo.com/maghodien/files/Vivi.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/17/01 12:06:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/21/2067621.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Scepter of Al'Kabor as a testing tool?</span><hr size=1> I imagine it is testing for luclin, if you look at previous artifact items in game (scaled claw of veeshan, the kneecrow robe) similar or better items have come out. I hope luclin has a staff like this... <p>Some say the world will end in fire;
